1
00:00:00,291 --> 00:00:02,375
There was a young man named

2
00:00:02,916 --> 00:00:05,875
Ahmad al-Lajji from Raqqa

3
00:00:06,166 --> 00:00:08,208
And another named Faisal al-Zaher

4
00:00:10,583 --> 00:00:13,333
And another named Ahmad al-Hamoud

5
00:00:13,541 --> 00:00:14,875
He was actually a child, not a young man

6
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:17,541
They were in solitary cells and we hadn’t spoken before

7
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:19,583
I didn’t even know they were in prison

8
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:23,291
They took them and lined them up in front of the group cell

9
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:28,166
In orange uniforms, with shaved heads and beards

10
00:00:30,750 --> 00:00:32,791
It happened on a Friday morning

11
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,000
They were asked about their charges

12
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:38,541
All of them were accused of collaborating with the Global Coalition

13
00:00:39,958 --> 00:00:44,875
One of them asked to write a will

14
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:47,666
So his debts could be paid, but they refused

15
00:00:49,166 --> 00:00:50,208
Then they took them away

16
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:53,000
I never saw them, only heard their voices

17
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,500
During torture sessions

18
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,666
I didn’t even know their names

19
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:59,750
Until they were called by name and I saw them then

20
00:01:01,791 --> 00:01:02,833
I used to see their writings on the walls

21
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:04,541
But I thought they had already been released

22
00:01:05,958 --> 00:01:08,208
Two days later

23
00:01:08,458 --> 00:01:12,958
A young man told me he had seen them killed in Tabqa

24
00:01:13,708 --> 00:01:15,625
Stabbed to death

25
00:01:16,125 --> 00:01:18,000
Then shot afterward

26
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,791
I told him I had seen them only once

27
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:29,208
Then they brought their magazine

28
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:34,375
It said they had executed agents of the Coalition

29
00:01:36,083 --> 00:01:40,583
Ahmad al-Lajji, Faisal al-Zaher, and Ahmad al-Hamoud

30
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:46,375
Our spirits would sink again every
time they took prisoners for execution

31
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:48,541
There was no taste for sleep or food

32
00:01:49,875 --> 00:01:53,458
When we thought of those killed, their families, and their children

33
00:01:53,708 --> 00:01:56,166
It became normal every two or three days

34
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:01,708
They would take women from the solitary cells

35
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:06,458
At night, carrying with them grave-digging tools

36
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:14,458
The vehicles would leave and come back

37
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:16,333
We saw the members smiling

38
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:19,083
As if they hadn’t just killed someone

39
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:22,708
And it kept happening

40
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:24,833
Every few days they would take one of the women

41
00:02:24,958 --> 00:02:28,916
There were five or six of them, maybe more
